==Finnish==
([[Wiktionary:Finnish_index_k|index K]])
===Etymology===
Derivative of ''[[kota]]''. It became "independent" from the case forms of that noun: In plural, one could say eg. in the [[illative]] ''Menen kotiin'', "I'll go to the tents"&mdash;there were many tents in a typical ancient settlement. The form was then reanalyzed as ''koti'' + ''-in'' and developed new plural forms, eg. the partitive: ''koteja''.
